==English==

===Etymology===
From the Greek [[ἀπό]] ("away, apart"), [[στάσις]] ("standing").

Also derived from Greek [[αποστάτης]], meaning "political rebel", as applied to rebellion against God, its law and the faith of Israel (in Hebrew [[מרד]]) in the old testament.

===Pronunciation===
a*pos"ta*sy

===Noun===
{{en-noun|apostasi|es}}

# {{rfv-sense}} Departure (spatial removal).
# The renunciation of a [[belief]] or set of beliefs.
# Specifically, the renunciation of one's [[religion]] or [[faith]].

====Synonyms====
*(''renunciation of religion or faith''): [[backsliding]], [[conversion]], [[deconversion]]
*(''renunciation of a set of beliefs''): [[defection]], [[disaffection]], [[estrangement]]

